RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUANA GALLO came in to bump rival nearing the eleven-sixteenths marker, responded when challenged by UNRIVALED QUEEN nearing the three-sixteenths pole, vied with that rival and held gamely. UNRIVALED QUEEN broke sharply then was bumped and checked nearing the eleven-sixteenths pole, moved up to offer a bid to the winner nearing the three-sixteenths marker, vied and just missed. CREME DE MENTHE was forwardly placed throughout, moved three-wide through the turn and finished evenly late. MS FLASHY HARBOR was off a step slow, lagged early, moved four-wide through the turn and did not offer a bid. THE RIDER OF UNRIVALED QUEEN LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST JUANA GALLO CONCERING THE BUMPING AND STEADYING OF HIS MOUNT AT THE ELEVEN-SIXTEENTHS POLE AND AFTER REVIEWING THE FILMS THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED JUANA GALLO FROM FIRST AND PLACED HER SECOND.
